The `AdminController.java` file contains the following information:

1.  **`@RequestMapping(value = "/admin/useed", method = RequestMethod.POST)`**: This annotation on the `useed()` method specifies the HTTP request path and the acceptable HTTP method.

Therefore, the full HTTP request path is `/admin/useed`, and only the POST method is acceptable. All other methods (HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, GET, PUT, DELETE, and PATCH) are not explicitly defined or supported by the code.
